# Project Overview - JSONPlaceholder Clone

This is a full-stack application that replicates JSONPlaceholder functionality with authentication and CRUD operations.

## Architecture
- **Frontend**: React 19 + TypeScript + Vite in [client/](mdc:client)
- **Backend**: NestJS + TypeScript + PostgreSQL in [server/](mdc:server)
- **Containerization**: Docker Compose setup in [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml)

## Key Entry Points
- **Frontend**: [client/src/main.tsx](mdc:client/src/main.tsx) - React app entry point
- **Backend**: [server/src/main.ts](mdc:server/src/main.ts) - NestJS app entry point
- **Main App Component**: [client/src/App.tsx](mdc:client/src/App.tsx) - Root React component
- **Backend Module**: [server/src/app.module.ts](mdc:server/src/app.module.ts) - Main NestJS module

## Quick Start Commands
- Frontend: `cd client && npm run dev` (runs on http://localhost:5173)
- Backend: `cd server && npm run start:dev` (runs on http://localhost:3000)
- Full Stack: `docker-compose up` (containerized deployment)

## Tech Stack Summary
- **Frontend**: React Query, React Router, Axios, Leaflet Maps, CSS Modules
- **Backend**: NestJS, TypeORM, PostgreSQL, JWT Auth, Passport, bcrypt
- **Testing**: Vitest (frontend), Jest (backend)
- **Development**: ESLint, Prettier, TypeScript
